  "prompt": "What is demographic dividend?",
  "response": "Demographic dividend refers to the economic growth potential that can arise from shifts in a country\u2019s population age structure, typically when the share of the working-age population (15-64 years) becomes larger than the non-working-age share of the population (young children and older adults). This change can provide a boost to economic productivity, provided there are policies in place that promote job creation, education, and healthcare.\n\nThe demographic dividend is not automatic; it requires investments in education, skill development, health care, and employment opportunities to truly reap the benefits. When countries successfully capitalize on this demographic shift, they experience higher economic growth and improved living standards.",
